In Paris, for example, travel organizations slept in tents in parks because our income did not allow us to pay the hotel or a pension.
The typical contract of a Czech travel was at this time to import its own preserved food, sauce, etc... to save.
Another important moment has also been the interoperability of the Czech crown that has allowed our tourists to buy free of the Western currency after decades.
Our standard of living and the average wage have increased what has caused another important moment around 1997.
With a growing demand for travel travel, travel agencies have started to prepare tours with air charter connections since 1997 which have formally reduced costs compared to what they had previously done.
At the end of the 1990s, the Czechs had visa-free links with practically most developed countries around the world with the EU, which later made our journeys easier.
Another moment of interest in the history of post-conflict tourism, when the first air charter was prepared for an exotic country, Thailand, from the Czech Republic.
