If the signals were resolved, it would no longer be necessary to repair approximately 200 thousand cases each rain season in the Metropolitan Valley area of Mexico, warns Rafael Herrera Nájera, researcher at the University of Chemistry (FQ) of UNAM, who has ensured that if the construction and maintenance process of the bitumen pipeline is adequate, the cases could be reduced or even completely eliminated.
