As the part of the pave that receives and distributes the effort, the rolling layer also requires that it has an adequate thickness and the material it is made must be cared for.
The climate, particularly humidity and temperature variations, is also a very important factor to consider, especially water, he says, because these significantly affect the performance of the asphalt layer.
When the soil melts, the water spreads inside the layer is difficult to produce, which brings back all layers of the floor and consequently causes cassies.
In the process of training a case, he said, the first one to be caught is the rolling film and only later the asphalt layer is affected, but the damage did not immediately occur, but it is a process that must be cared for by the first signals with appropriate care programs.
